I'd faint from hunger for missing a meal.

24
00:02:12,550 --> 00:02:13,700
It's dinner time.

25
00:02:13,700 --> 00:02:15,910
Get something for your stomach.

26
00:02:15,910 --> 00:02:17,619
I thought you weren't going to come.

27
00:02:17,619 --> 00:02:19,500
Let me heat these dishes for you.

28
00:02:19,500 --> 00:02:21,600
Don't bother.

29
00:02:21,600 --> 00:02:23,800
Let's eat.

30
00:02:23,800 --> 00:02:25,200
Okay.

31
00:02:41,270 --> 00:02:43,170
So, you went to see her.

32
00:02:48,270 --> 00:02:50,490
Was she happy to see you?

33
00:03:03,760 --> 00:03:05,760
Your mom

34
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:10,500
has been like that.

35
00:03:10,500 --> 00:03:12,700
She has good and bad days.

36
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:16,220
It's not your problem.

37
00:03:16,220 --> 00:03:17,920
Don't take it to...

38
00:03:22,400 --> 00:03:26,300
I mean, we're getting old.

39
00:03:26,300 --> 00:03:29,900
Sometimes, we can't remember clearly our past.

40
00:03:29,900 --> 00:03:32,000
Especially for her.

41
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:34,190
We failed as parents.

42
00:03:34,190 --> 00:03:36,360
None of this is your fault.

43
00:03:41,500 --> 00:03:43,300
Have some cabbages.

44
00:03:43,300 --> 00:03:45,600
These are from my gardens, very organic.

45
00:03:47,880 --> 00:03:49,810
I hate cabbages.

46
00:04:03,160 --> 00:04:04,760
Well...

47
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:09,600
When you two met,

48
00:04:10,140 --> 00:04:12,240
did you talk about anything?

49
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:16,640
You have so many questions.

50
00:04:16,640 --> 00:04:18,820
Why don't you ask her yourself?

51
00:04:29,640 --> 00:04:31,540
I'm full.

52
00:04:31,540 --> 00:04:32,950
Thanks.

53
00:04:32,950 --> 00:04:34,650
Jiahui!

54
00:04:37,130 --> 00:04:38,930
Jiahui!

55
00:04:40,380 --> 00:04:41,980
Jiahui!

56
00:04:42,730 --> 00:04:44,330
Jiahui!

57
00:04:45,070 --> 00:04:47,160
Are you my son?

58
00:04:56,130 --> 00:04:57,830
I have a father.

59
00:05:00,510 --> 00:05:02,740
You got your own life.

60
00:05:02,740 --> 00:05:04,530
I got mine.

61
00:05:05,920 --> 00:05:08,740
Don't bother doing anything for me.

62
00:05:08,740 --> 00:05:11,640
The best way for us to get along

63
00:05:12,940 --> 00:05:15,180
is to get away from each other.

64
00:06:30,580 --> 00:06:37,180
[Tomb of Beloved Son Hejun]

65
00:06:43,410 --> 00:06:45,210
Jun Jun,

66
00:06:45,960 --> 00:06:47,760
it's mom.

67
00:06:48,340 --> 00:06:51,590
It seems you've grown up a little.

68
00:06:51,590 --> 00:06:53,440
You haven't?

69
00:06:53,440 --> 00:06:55,760
Have I grown old?

70
00:06:57,640 --> 00:06:59,620
I haven't?

71
00:07:00,250 --> 00:07:02,820
Look what I got for you.

72
00:07:02,820 --> 00:07:06,540
Do you remember the sunflowers in our yard?

73
00:07:06,540 --> 00:07:08,339
You wanted to pick some every time you walked by there.

74
00:07:08,339 --> 00:07:12,350
I'd prevent you from going ahead. I told you to respect all living things.

75
00:07:12,350 --> 00:07:14,350
I know you like this smell.

76
00:07:14,350 --> 00:07:15,750
Smell it.

77
00:07:15,750 --> 00:07:20,200
Do they smell as they used to?

78
00:07:21,340 --> 00:07:23,040
Right?

79
00:07:31,900 --> 00:07:34,490
I got you another surprise.

80
00:07:37,220 --> 00:07:38,390
See?

81
00:07:38,390 --> 00:07:41,560
When you were a kid, your favorite food was cream cake.

82
00:07:41,560 --> 00:07:44,301
Do you know why I'd prevent you from eating cakes?

83
00:07:44,301 --> 00:07:46,550
Because you'd skip meals for cakes.

84
00:07:46,550 --> 00:07:49,000
If you don't eat well, how can you grow taller into a big boy?

85
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:50,059
Right?

86
00:07:50,059 --> 00:07:54,610
Now, you don't need to grow any taller.

87
00:07:55,570 --> 00:07:58,360
So, I bring some cakes for you. Enjoy.

88
00:07:58,360 --> 00:07:59,670
Have a taste.

89
00:07:59,670 --> 00:08:01,230
I made them myself.

90
00:08:01,230 --> 00:08:03,480
If you like it,

91
00:08:03,480 --> 00:08:06,820
I'd come here with cakes more often.

92
00:08:06,820 --> 00:08:08,420
Okay?

93
00:08:14,130 --> 00:08:17,170
I got another thing you like.

94
00:08:21,160 --> 00:08:22,390
I never got it back then.

95
00:08:22,390 --> 00:08:27,160
I didn't understand why you'd bring it with you everywhere, even to your bed.

96
00:08:27,160 --> 00:08:29,940
As a man, I'm going to protect my family,

97
00:08:29,940 --> 00:08:31,830
speak my mind, and keep my word.

98
00:08:31,830 --> 00:08:32,859
This is my way of acting like a Ninja.

99
00:08:32,859 --> 00:08:35,249
I was silly. After your death,

100
00:08:35,249 --> 00:08:40,330
I kept it with me as something to remember you by.

101
00:08:40,330 --> 00:08:41,419
I was wrong.

102
00:08:41,419 --> 00:08:43,080
This is your treasured object.

103
00:08:43,080 --> 00:08:44,910
You're the one who likes it.

104
00:08:44,910 --> 00:08:46,730
So, I bring it to you today.

105
00:08:46,730 --> 00:08:48,670
It will stay with you.

106
00:08:48,670 --> 00:08:51,130
I put it here.

107
00:09:00,740 --> 00:09:02,440
Jun Jun,

108
00:09:04,230 --> 00:09:07,010
you must be mad at me.

109
00:09:07,010 --> 00:09:08,790
You have all the reasons to be mad at me.

110
00:09:08,790 --> 00:09:10,659
You must blame me

111
00:09:10,659 --> 00:09:15,070
for not protecting you from falling into the water,

112
00:09:15,070 --> 00:09:18,320
for not holding your hands firmly enough when you were swept away by water.

113
00:09:18,320 --> 00:09:19,299
Right?

114
00:09:19,299 --> 00:09:22,600
It really was my fault. I'm sorry.

115
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:26,770
I failed as a mother.

116
00:09:26,770 --> 00:09:32,710
After your death, for millions of times, I thought

117
00:09:32,710 --> 00:09:38,460
if only I was the one who got swept away by water.

118
00:09:38,460 --> 00:09:40,400
However, I got but two hands.

119
00:09:40,400 --> 00:09:42,249
There was no way I could save you both.

120
00:09:42,249 --> 00:09:47,030
I was planning to come back for you after saving your sister.

121
00:09:47,030 --> 00:09:48,470
But you were just a little kid.

122
00:09:48,470 --> 00:09:50,129
You were trapped in a dark place.

123
00:09:50,129 --> 00:09:52,900
You must be so scared

124
00:09:52,900 --> 00:09:55,140
and hate me so much

125
00:09:55,140 --> 00:09:57,990
when I failed to appear.

126
00:09:59,910 --> 00:10:02,950
I hate myself for that, too.

127
00:10:02,950 --> 00:10:08,290
Do you know why I didn't kill myself?

128
00:10:08,290 --> 00:10:09,760
It's not that I'm afraid of death.

129
00:10:09,760 --> 00:10:12,980
No. I want to see you so much.

130
00:10:12,980 --> 00:10:15,800
You see, I'm not only your mother.

131
00:10:15,800 --> 00:10:19,350
I'm also the mother of your sister.

132
00:10:19,350 --> 00:10:21,029
Your sister was also a kid back then.

133
00:10:21,029 --> 00:10:24,100
I just couldn't imagine her growing up without a mother.

134
00:10:24,100 --> 00:10:26,920
I would worry if she got bullied at school,

135
00:10:26,920 --> 00:10:31,130
if she failed to focus on school or if she fell in love too young.

136
00:10:31,130 --> 00:10:34,300
She is going to need my advice on her romantic relationship,

137
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:38,340
marriage and parenting skills.

138
00:10:38,340 --> 00:10:39,940
You see,

139
00:10:41,180 --> 00:10:46,470
you don't need that anymore.

140
00:10:46,470 --> 00:10:51,200
Jun Jun, you don't have the chance to be mischievous,

141
00:10:51,200 --> 00:10:54,580
to experience puppy love,

142
00:10:54,580 --> 00:10:58,030
to find a girlfriend,

143
00:10:58,930 --> 00:11:01,940
to get married.

144
00:11:01,940 --> 00:11:05,520
You don't need me anymore.

145
00:11:05,520 --> 00:11:10,440
I don't need to worry about you anymore.

146
00:11:10,440 --> 00:11:13,760
I know

147
00:11:13,760 --> 00:11:18,880
you're a good boy now.

148
00:11:21,370 --> 00:11:24,680
I have another reason. You see,

149
00:11:26,050 --> 00:11:28,929
because of your death,

150
00:11:28,929 --> 00:11:30,779
your dad and sister had a nervous breakdown.

151
00:11:30,779 --> 00:11:33,890
I was worried about your father.

152
00:11:35,490 --> 00:11:38,240
That's why

153
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:41,690
I chose to stay.

154
00:11:41,690 --> 00:11:43,570
Jun Jun,

155
00:11:43,570 --> 00:11:47,100
perhaps you don't understand what I'm saying.

156
00:11:47,100 --> 00:11:49,180
You're just a kid.

157
00:11:49,740 --> 00:11:54,550
You only need to understand one thing.

158
00:11:54,550 --> 00:11:56,190
That is,

159
00:11:56,840 --> 00:11:58,440
I...

160
00:11:59,910 --> 00:12:01,710
loves you

161
00:12:02,780 --> 00:12:04,580
very, very much.

162
00:12:06,900 --> 00:12:11,230
I just can't love you enough.

163
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:26,520
Go, go, go.

164
00:12:26,520 --> 00:12:28,220
There you go. There you go. Hold your position.

165
00:12:28,220 --> 00:12:30,780
Keep your back straight.

166
00:12:30,780 --> 00:12:32,480
Breathe. Breathe.

167
00:12:32,480 --> 00:12:34,010
Two more to go. One.

168
00:12:34,010 --> 00:12:36,180
Put it down slowly. Put it down slowly. There you go.

169
00:12:36,180 --> 00:12:38,580
I can't do it!

170
00:12:38,580 --> 00:12:40,530
- One more to go.
- I'm exhausted.

171
00:12:40,530 --> 00:12:42,690
I'm exhausted.

172
00:12:42,690 --> 00:12:44,510
My legs are so weak.

173
00:12:48,550 --> 00:12:51,050
Your mom called.

174
00:12:51,910 --> 00:12:52,979
You don't want to call her back?

175
00:12:52,979 --> 00:12:54,580
No need.

176
00:12:54,580 --> 00:12:57,570
What happened? Did you have a fight?

177
00:12:57,570 --> 00:12:59,240
We are good.

178
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:10,709
Come on.

179
00:13:10,709 --> 00:13:14,130
Lili, you need to learn to take care of yourself.

180
00:13:20,790 --> 00:13:23,180
Mr. Jin Tao, actually, I'm pretty good at it.

181
00:13:23,180 --> 00:13:27,330
But answer my question. Why does a girl need a boyfriend if she can do everything on her own?

182
00:13:32,520 --> 00:13:34,650
I didn't mean that.

183
00:13:44,910 --> 00:13:47,180
I signed up for you here for one year.

184
00:13:47,180 --> 00:13:50,350
Next time, let's go to the gym together.

185
00:13:50,350 --> 00:13:51,910
Lili, don't waste your money.

186
00:13:51,910 --> 00:13:53,900
I don't need it.

187
00:13:54,570 --> 00:13:56,070
Okay.

188
00:13:57,880 --> 00:13:58,739
Do you need gym card?

189
00:13:58,739 --> 00:14:01,251
This card is for one year at the gym. It's for free. Do you want it?

190
00:14:02,300 --> 00:14:03,620
Excuse me.

191
00:14:03,620 --> 00:14:05,200
So, if you don't want it, no one can have it?

192
00:14:05,200 --> 00:14:07,110
Don't be so capricious, okay?

193
00:14:07,110 --> 00:14:09,800
You're not getting any younger. Don't be capricious.

194
00:14:09,800 --> 00:14:12,310
I just want us to spend more time together.

195
00:14:12,310 --> 00:14:13,809
Is there anything wrong with that?

196
00:14:13,809 --> 00:14:15,110
What's wrong with you today?

197
00:14:15,110 --> 00:14:17,910
Why don't we cut right to it?

198
00:14:17,910 --> 00:14:19,410
Never mind.

199
00:14:26,470 --> 00:14:30,420
Jin Tao, tell me the truth.

200
00:14:30,420 --> 00:14:32,250
Your parents don't like me, do they?

201
00:14:32,250 --> 00:14:36,010
Of course, they do. They like you very much.

202
00:14:36,010 --> 00:14:38,010
It's just

203
00:14:40,610 --> 00:14:42,260
I'll be gone for a while.

204
00:14:42,260 --> 00:14:43,700
What you do mean?

205
00:14:43,700 --> 00:14:45,490
Did I upset you by being capricious?

206
00:14:45,490 --> 00:14:46,729
Not at all.

207
00:14:46,729 --> 00:14:48,301
Then what on earth do you mean? Tell me.

208
00:14:48,301 --> 00:14:49,659
Why are you being so evasive?

209
00:14:49,659 --> 00:14:52,180
I can't explain.

210
00:14:59,150 --> 00:15:01,350
It's complicated.

211
00:15:01,350 --> 00:15:04,980
I think it's better for both of us to take a break.

212
00:15:11,930 --> 00:15:13,650
Did I get you upset?

213
00:15:13,650 --> 00:15:15,780
Not at all.

214
00:15:17,910 --> 00:15:21,570
Do you know why I get to do things in my own way?

215
00:15:21,570 --> 00:15:24,490
Because no one ever asked me to take responsibility.

216
00:15:28,780 --> 00:15:30,280
Lili!

217
00:16:01,220 --> 00:16:03,020
You're here.

218
00:16:07,980 --> 00:16:10,250
Whose kid is Jiahui?

219
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:19,400
Fei Fei is obviously my kid.

220
00:16:39,570 --> 00:16:41,790
Who is his father?

221
00:16:44,010 --> 00:16:45,710
Let go of me!

222
00:16:54,470 --> 00:16:56,770
Were you pregnant

223
00:16:57,370 --> 00:16:59,640
when you left me?

224
00:17:06,780 --> 00:17:08,880
Is he my child?

225
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:13,940
Is he my child?

226
00:17:18,630 --> 00:17:21,629
Let go of me! Let go of me!

227
00:17:21,629 --> 00:17:23,930
Mom! Mom! Mom!

228
00:17:33,880 --> 00:17:36,970
- Fu Tang! Fu Tang! Okay, okay, I stop asking.
- Professor Ji. Professor Ji.

229
00:17:36,970 --> 00:17:39,249
It's okay. It's okay.

230
00:17:39,249 --> 00:17:40,419
Let's go back.

231
00:17:40,419 --> 00:17:41,920
It's okay.

232
00:17:42,900 --> 00:17:45,220
Professor Ji, you need to play it cool.

233
00:17:45,220 --> 00:17:48,040
Let her get some rest.

234
00:19:08,370 --> 00:19:11,730
Auntie Fu, are you writing something?

235
00:19:17,010 --> 00:19:18,910
I forgot.

236
00:19:20,590 --> 00:19:23,520
It's okay. Don't push yourself.

237
00:19:23,520 --> 00:19:25,380
Do you want a candy?

238
00:19:25,380 --> 00:19:27,310
See?

239
00:19:27,310 --> 00:19:29,000
Your favorite candy.

240
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:31,179
Last time we were here,

241
00:19:31,179 --> 00:19:35,010
you said you'd let us know the end of the story.

242
00:19:35,010 --> 00:19:36,059
That's right.

243
00:19:36,059 --> 00:19:38,689
Childhood sweetheart and love at first sight, what was her final decision?

244
00:19:38,689 --> 00:19:40,770
Just give us some hints.

245
00:19:40,770 --> 00:19:43,160
Even the TV show has a preview.

246
00:19:43,160 --> 00:19:46,180
You just wouldn't give us a clue.

247
00:19:46,180 --> 00:19:51,540
The story must go on till it gets to the end.

248
00:19:51,540 --> 00:19:53,580
Then, let's keep on playing, okay?

249
00:19:53,580 --> 00:19:57,280
This time, I want to play another character.

250
00:20:05,820 --> 00:20:07,820
It's raining outside.

251
00:20:12,370 --> 00:20:14,070
What are you doing here?

252
00:20:14,920 --> 00:20:16,720
I'm here to see you.

253
00:20:17,370 --> 00:20:20,110
I told you not to come.

254
00:20:21,400 --> 00:20:25,810
You never meant it.

255
00:20:25,810 --> 00:20:27,860
I really meant it.

256
00:20:27,860 --> 00:20:30,480
I hate those who didn't keep their promises.

257
00:20:30,480 --> 00:20:33,941
You just hate it when people failed to keep their promises to you.

258
00:20:39,210 --> 00:20:41,270
Are you judging me?

259
00:20:41,270 --> 00:20:43,300
Not at all.

260
00:20:43,300 --> 00:20:45,420
I mean,

261
00:20:46,180 --> 00:20:47,680
it's raining

262
00:20:48,780 --> 00:20:50,480
outside.

263
00:20:51,590 --> 00:20:53,820
I don't want you to catch a cold.

264
00:20:53,820 --> 00:20:57,061
What I hate most is hypocrisy.

265
00:21:10,660 --> 00:21:13,170
I understand why you're mad.

266
00:21:13,170 --> 00:21:15,750
I haven't finished collecting the data of the phase II trial.

267
00:21:15,750 --> 00:21:19,440
No one can be sure about the side effects of the drug.

268
00:21:19,440 --> 00:21:21,820
Science is a serious subject.

269
00:21:21,820 --> 00:21:23,720
It has to be precise.

270
00:21:23,720 --> 00:21:25,700
Especially for you.

271
00:21:26,590 --> 00:21:29,520
You have no confidence in your drugs.

272
00:21:35,380 --> 00:21:37,510
Can't it wait?

273
00:21:42,190 --> 00:21:45,270
It's like you don't know me at all.

274
00:22:31,180 --> 00:22:33,220
Do you really want to give it a try?

