00:22:43,580 --> 00:22:46,070
You don't like this story, do you?

276
00:22:47,000 --> 00:22:51,360
Well. This is your story. I don't get a say in this.

277
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:55,400
It's just that I feel a little sorry for this man.

278
00:22:56,560 --> 00:22:58,580
You do?

279
00:22:58,580 --> 00:23:00,991
Don't you think this man doesn't know her at all?

280
00:23:00,991 --> 00:23:02,750
Why do you ask that?

281
00:23:03,940 --> 00:23:08,530
They are more alike no matter in their personalities,

282
00:23:08,530 --> 00:23:11,080
family backgrounds or many other things.

283
00:23:14,820 --> 00:23:17,230
They belong to the same world.

284
00:23:17,230 --> 00:23:19,230
I'm not too sure I agree with that.

285
00:23:19,230 --> 00:23:21,520
Who says two similar people are meant to be together?

286
00:23:21,520 --> 00:23:24,820
For me, what matters in a relationship is that the two people like each other.

287
00:23:24,820 --> 00:23:26,220
Right?

288
00:23:27,880 --> 00:23:31,780
They are like a pair of hedgehogs.

289
00:23:31,780 --> 00:23:35,290
Standing back in back, they'd hurt each other.

290
00:23:37,970 --> 00:23:40,310
However, once they turn around,

291
00:23:41,300 --> 00:23:44,110
they'd find each other's gentle side.

292
00:23:45,010 --> 00:23:46,610
Well,

293
00:23:47,660 --> 00:23:50,020
that's the part of a story to be recounted later.

294
00:23:57,370 --> 00:23:59,670
What are you doing?

295
00:23:59,670 --> 00:24:01,670
I just bought this digital camera.

296
00:24:01,670 --> 00:24:03,340
I know it's a digital camera.

297
00:24:03,340 --> 00:24:05,029
I'm asking what you are doing with that.

298
00:24:05,029 --> 00:24:07,560
Recording my study subject.

299
00:24:07,560 --> 00:24:11,060
I accepted the offer on one condition

300
00:24:11,060 --> 00:24:13,540
that I'll make a case study out of your case.

301
00:24:13,540 --> 00:24:16,060
You're free to quit

302
00:24:16,060 --> 00:24:17,960
if it makes you uncomfortable.

303
00:24:19,850 --> 00:24:22,310
That makes me your guinea pig.

304
00:24:22,310 --> 00:24:23,900
Rather, a volunteer.

305
00:24:23,900 --> 00:24:26,090
Will this video

306
00:24:27,420 --> 00:24:28,920
be made public?

307
00:24:28,920 --> 00:24:29,969
Don't worry.

308
00:24:29,969 --> 00:24:32,540
This is for psychological research purpose.

309
00:24:32,540 --> 00:24:35,501
I'm probably the only one who gets to watch this video.

310
00:24:35,501 --> 00:24:39,640
I'm obliged to keep your case confidential.

311
00:24:46,200 --> 00:24:47,900
Hold on.

312
00:24:57,110 --> 00:24:59,060
Let's get started.

313
00:25:00,820 --> 00:25:03,970
Let's call it a day.

314
00:25:03,970 --> 00:25:06,050
Before ending our session today,

315
00:25:06,050 --> 00:25:09,400
I want you to promise me that for the following sessions,

316
00:25:09,400 --> 00:25:12,610
you'll eat and sleep at regular times

317
00:25:12,610 --> 00:25:14,810
and won't hurt yourself.

318
00:25:14,810 --> 00:25:16,780
Can you promise me that?

319
00:25:18,590 --> 00:25:20,590
Can you do that for me?

320
00:25:24,230 --> 00:25:26,430
You've asked me so many questions.

321
00:25:26,430 --> 00:25:28,800
Can I ask you one question?

322
00:25:32,350 --> 00:25:33,750
What question?

323
00:25:33,750 --> 00:25:37,620
Keep holding that digital camera.

324
00:25:42,310 --> 00:25:43,910
Please go ahead.

325
00:25:45,660 --> 00:25:47,830
Let's date.

326
00:25:57,190 --> 00:25:59,520
No.

327
00:25:59,520 --> 00:26:01,320
Why?

328
00:26:02,760 --> 00:26:04,060
No reason.

329
00:26:04,060 --> 00:26:07,050
This is against the rules.

330
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:11,680
I'm your psychiatrist.

331
00:26:12,760 --> 00:26:15,260
I like breaking rules.

332
00:26:18,870 --> 00:26:21,430
Don't you want to date me?

333
00:26:22,300 --> 00:26:24,420
I just want to cure your disease.

334
00:26:24,420 --> 00:26:26,590
You're avoiding the issue.

335
00:26:31,370 --> 00:26:32,970
I'm not.

336
00:26:40,970 --> 00:26:43,110
Then promise me

337
00:26:44,590 --> 00:26:47,560
that we'll be together when I'm cured.

338
00:26:55,110 --> 00:26:58,710
When I look back on my life,

339
00:26:58,710 --> 00:27:02,540
it seems he was standing at the fork of each road,

340
00:27:03,540 --> 00:27:08,540
smiling at me like a loyal solider.

341
00:27:08,540 --> 00:27:11,120
It's just that

342
00:27:12,180 --> 00:27:14,720
I never picked him once.

343
00:28:26,300 --> 00:28:28,930
Is this a reward for me?

344
00:28:30,350 --> 00:28:32,700
You're in good condition these days.

345
00:28:39,710 --> 00:28:44,600
So, are we in a relationship now?

346
00:28:46,490 --> 00:28:48,810
I just want to cure your disease.

347
00:28:52,260 --> 00:28:55,600
Can't you tell I'm already cured?

348
00:29:02,400 --> 00:29:05,700
Is it safe for her to use a scissor?

349
00:29:05,700 --> 00:29:08,580
Actually, we should have confiscated such things.

350
00:29:08,580 --> 00:29:11,359
But characteristically, even if we hide it somewhere,

351
00:29:11,359 --> 00:29:14,610
she'd find it anyway.

352
00:29:33,490 --> 00:29:35,290
It's for you.

353
00:29:37,300 --> 00:29:39,249
"I have nothing to offer you"

354
00:29:39,249 --> 00:29:41,240
The next line is?

355
00:29:41,240 --> 00:29:44,600
"I have nothing to offer you but a blossom branch from my hometown in the spring time"

356
00:29:44,600 --> 00:29:48,010
What does it mean, Mom?

357
00:29:48,010 --> 00:29:51,500
There was this poet named Lu Kai.

358
00:29:51,500 --> 00:29:54,490
He had a good friend whose name was Fan Ye.

359
00:29:54,490 --> 00:29:57,130
They were very good friends. However, they lived very far apart.

360
00:29:57,130 --> 00:30:00,680
One lived in the south while the other lived in the north.

361
00:30:00,680 --> 00:30:04,610
They'd express how much they miss each other. In their letters.

362
00:30:04,610 --> 00:30:07,300
One day, Lu Kai ran into a postman.

363
00:30:07,300 --> 00:30:12,090
He asked the postman to deliver a letter to his friend.

364
00:30:12,090 --> 00:30:14,129
But what to write about?

365
00:30:14,129 --> 00:30:17,440
While he was pondering this, plum blossoms greeted his eyes.

366
00:30:17,440 --> 00:30:21,970
So, he picked a blossom branch and wrote this poem.

367
00:30:21,970 --> 00:30:27,090
"I have nothing to offer you but a blossom branch from my hometown in the spring time"

368
00:30:27,090 --> 00:30:32,101
He wanted his friend to have a glimpse of the springtime in the regions south of the Yangtze River.

369
00:30:51,370 --> 00:30:52,609
Thanks.

370
00:30:52,609 --> 00:30:54,310
It's beautiful.

371
00:31:00,970 --> 00:31:02,770
What happened then?

372
00:31:03,700 --> 00:31:07,470
How would you like this story to develop?

373
00:31:09,960 --> 00:31:11,960
Well,

374
00:31:16,460 --> 00:31:21,580
one day, the girl was found to

375
00:31:21,580 --> 00:31:24,280
take pills secretly.

376
00:31:24,280 --> 00:31:26,740
So, it's true you've been drugging her.

377
00:31:26,740 --> 00:31:29,729
Can't you see she's getting much better?

378
00:31:29,729 --> 00:31:33,160
Shouldn't you let me know before giving her pills?

379
00:31:34,330 --> 00:31:36,030
Why should I?

380
00:31:36,030 --> 00:31:38,070
Who do you think you are?

381
00:31:42,610 --> 00:31:45,590
You also gave her this drug, right?

382
00:31:55,060 --> 00:31:58,670
Listen, the bottle has no information on it.

383
00:31:58,670 --> 00:32:03,210
I need you to explain to me the name and ingredients of this drug.

384
00:32:03,210 --> 00:32:06,610
Otherwise, I'll report you to the SFDA for illegal drug use.

385
00:32:06,610 --> 00:32:08,750
You're committing a crime!

386
00:32:10,420 --> 00:32:12,660
Are you threatening me?

387
00:32:12,660 --> 00:32:14,920
You're despicable.

388
00:32:14,920 --> 00:32:18,320
Did you know your treatment never worked on her?

389
00:32:18,320 --> 00:32:21,631
Did you know she tried to kill herself the other day?

390
00:32:22,510 --> 00:32:23,999
That's not true.

391
00:32:24,000 --> 00:32:26,250
That's true!

392
00:32:26,250 --> 00:32:30,590
How could you ignore such obvious mood swings?

393
00:32:32,360 --> 00:32:34,470
So, the psychiatrist believed

394
00:32:34,470 --> 00:32:36,990
he has helped the girl feel better.

395
00:32:36,990 --> 00:32:42,090
But the pharmacist thought the girl would have killed herself but for his drugs.

396
00:32:44,250 --> 00:32:46,970
After that fight,

397
00:32:46,970 --> 00:32:50,120
the rivals in love

398
00:32:50,730 --> 00:32:55,380
started to accuse each other and became sworn enemies.

399
00:32:57,370 --> 00:32:59,470
What happened then?

400
00:32:59,470 --> 00:33:01,950
Did that girl get recovered?

401
00:33:03,250 --> 00:33:04,950
Of course, she did.

402
00:33:04,950 --> 00:33:06,650
But...

403
00:33:07,400 --> 00:33:09,100
But?

404
00:33:11,700 --> 00:33:14,940
News report. Sikang Pharmaceuticals announced early this morning

405
00:33:14,940 --> 00:33:18,630
the termination of the research and development of a new drug for bipolar disorder.

406
00:33:18,630 --> 00:33:20,419
According to a supervisory organization,

407
00:33:20,419 --> 00:33:23,900
some clinical trial patients showed serious adverse reactions to the drug,

408
00:33:23,900 --> 00:33:26,010
including memory impairment and confusion,

409
00:33:26,010 --> 00:33:28,180
which led to protests from patients and their families.

410
00:33:28,180 --> 00:33:31,730
Now, the research and development of the drug have been suspended at all levels.

411
00:33:31,730 --> 00:33:33,630
It can't be true.

412
00:33:34,850 --> 00:33:36,450
It can't be true.

413
00:33:36,450 --> 00:33:40,681
They told me they were about to pass the phase II of the clinical trial.

414
00:33:48,850 --> 00:33:51,040
I was framed.

415
00:34:03,180 --> 00:34:05,760
I will find a solution.

416
00:34:41,170 --> 00:34:45,460
It seems to me you always wear a red dress.

417
00:34:45,460 --> 00:34:47,900
This has never changed.

418
00:34:51,660 --> 00:34:53,660
Do you like it?

419
00:34:54,660 --> 00:34:56,260
Yes.

420
00:35:16,660 --> 00:35:17,709
Excuse me.

421
00:35:17,709 --> 00:35:19,880
Can I get a face mask?

422
00:35:21,280 --> 00:35:22,770
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

423
00:35:22,770 --> 00:35:24,569
When I was at the entry,

424
00:35:24,569 --> 00:35:27,520
I saw a person in the hospital gown looking for someone.

425
00:35:27,520 --> 00:35:30,340
I thought this place has an entrance guard.

426
00:35:30,340 --> 00:35:31,860
Crap.

427
00:35:41,020 --> 00:35:42,600
[Fu Tang]

428
00:35:58,770 --> 00:36:00,690
This is for you.

429
00:36:00,690 --> 00:36:02,740
Where are we now?

430
00:36:02,740 --> 00:36:07,700
You mean, you can have it because we are sort of related?

431
00:36:30,080 --> 00:36:31,980
Your parents don't like me, do they?

432
00:36:31,980 --> 00:36:34,980
Of course, they do. They like you very much.

433
00:36:35,670 --> 00:36:37,470
It's just

434
00:36:39,000 --> 00:36:41,290
I'll be gone for a while.

435
00:36:58,760 --> 00:37:00,730
Both of them are nice.

436
00:37:00,730 --> 00:37:03,160
That's a dangerous thought.

437
00:37:03,160 --> 00:37:04,460
She has to choose from them.

438
00:37:04,460 --> 00:37:07,910
Otherwise, the story will end in tragedy.

439
00:37:07,910 --> 00:37:10,260
Whom would you choose if that were you?

440
00:37:10,260 --> 00:37:11,269
I'm not her.

441
00:37:11,269 --> 00:37:13,129
I can't make the decision for her.

442
00:37:13,129 --> 00:37:16,660
Would you analyze it as a female psychiatrist?

443
00:37:17,460 --> 00:37:22,870
It seems the girl thinks favorably of the psychiatrist.

444
00:37:26,220 --> 00:37:29,550
Jiahui, are you all right?

445
00:37:29,550 --> 00:37:31,230
I'm fine.

446
00:37:31,230 --> 00:37:32,419
What do you think?

447
00:37:32,419 --> 00:37:34,680
Whom do you think the girl will choose?

448
00:37:35,530 --> 00:37:38,221
It seems she'll choose neither of them.

449
00:37:38,221 --> 00:37:39,820
Why?

450
00:37:43,460 --> 00:37:49,900
In this world, she has the right to love anyone, and not to love anyone.

451
00:37:49,900 --> 00:37:52,660
She is not to be a prisoner of love.

452
00:37:54,810 --> 00:37:59,150
Perhaps she loves no one but herself and freedom.

453
00:38:00,740 --> 00:38:03,330
Jiahui, may I ask you a question?

454
00:38:03,330 --> 00:38:05,160
Go ahead.

455
00:38:05,160 --> 00:38:07,800
Is that pharmacist your foster father?

456
00:38:18,700 --> 00:38:20,700
Professor Ji.

457
00:38:20,700 --> 00:38:22,970
What brings you here?

458
00:38:22,970 --> 00:38:24,770
Drop the vegetables. Come on.

459
00:38:24,770 --> 00:38:26,170
Let's cook dumplings.

460
00:38:26,170 --> 00:38:29,770
Aren't you a king at home?

461
00:38:29,770 --> 00:38:31,370
See,

462
00:38:32,460 --> 00:38:33,739
shrimp dumplings, a hit product.

463
00:38:33,739 --> 00:38:35,219
It contains shrimps and vegetables.

464
00:38:35,219 --> 00:38:37,420
It can save a lot of time and trouble. Let's go.

465
00:38:37,420 --> 00:38:40,410
Come on, you lazy guy.

466
00:38:40,410 --> 00:38:42,070
Let's go.

467
00:38:42,070 --> 00:38:45,070
Old Zhang, take a seat.

468
00:38:51,280 --> 00:38:53,220
You have a son, don't you?

469
00:38:53,220 --> 00:38:54,569
How old is he?

470
00:38:54,569 --> 00:38:56,570
Twenty-nine.

471
00:38:58,090 --> 00:39:02,390
Is it hard to discipline kids of that age?

472
00:39:02,390 --> 00:39:04,500
You call a 29-year-old man kid?

473
00:39:04,500 --> 00:39:06,220
Discipline them?

474
00:39:06,220 --> 00:39:07,680
How?

475
00:39:07,680 --> 00:39:09,340
He is going to start a family.

476
00:39:09,340 --> 00:39:10,910
There is nothing I can do.

477
00:39:12,130 --> 00:39:14,980
I just want to know

478
00:39:14,980 --> 00:39:18,560
how I should get along with them.

479
00:39:18,560 --> 00:39:20,570
You mean my son and I?

480
00:39:20,570 --> 00:39:22,630
There is no specific ways.

481
00:39:22,630 --> 00:39:24,850
We can sit together for a whole day without saying anything.

482
00:39:24,850 --> 00:39:27,430
It's the bond between a father and his son.

483
00:39:27,430 --> 00:39:30,460
Perhaps you have nothing to say to each other.

484
00:39:30,460 --> 00:39:34,450
That's better than saying mean things to each other, right?

485
00:39:34,450 --> 00:39:37,710
It's nicer when people just get along.

486
00:39:38,660 --> 00:39:40,260
Wait a moment.

487
00:39:41,640 --> 00:39:43,640
What do you mean by that?

488
00:39:43,640 --> 00:39:46,910
What? Don't point your fingers at me.

489
00:39:46,910 --> 00:39:49,780
Do you have a crush on someone?

490
00:39:49,780 --> 00:39:52,330
And she has an adult son?

491
00:39:52,900 --> 00:39:56,520
Come on, at my age, that's not happening.

492
00:39:56,520 --> 00:39:59,000
I'm just curious.

493
00:40:01,020 --> 00:40:03,550
It seems you don't get to enjoy the happy family time.

494
00:40:03,550 --> 00:40:06,130
My son is getting married this year.

495
00:40:06,130 --> 00:40:09,510
Perhaps I'll have a grandson next year.

496
00:40:09,510 --> 00:40:11,530
Hey, I've got a plan.

497
00:40:11,530 --> 00:40:14,940
I'll take care of the baby three days a week.

498
00:40:14,940 --> 00:40:17,260
When the baby grows older, he'll live with me.

499
00:40:17,260 --> 00:40:19,129
I'll teach him on my own.

500
00:40:19,129 --> 00:40:21,930
That will save the tuition fee for preschool education.

501
00:40:21,930 --> 00:40:23,499
All right, give it a rest.

502
00:40:23,499 --> 00:40:25,110
Go cook the dumplings.

503
00:40:25,110 --> 00:40:27,800
All right, wait right here.

504
00:40:34,480 --> 00:40:37,420
I need you to sign here.

505
00:40:40,940 --> 00:40:43,660
Mr. Ye, I told you before,

506
00:40:43,660 --> 00:40:46,320
I was working on the promotion of pilot projects of group counseling.

507
00:40:46,320 --> 00:40:48,229
The association has approved the budget.

508
00:40:48,229 --> 00:40:50,119
Opening shops in the communities

509
00:40:50,119 --> 00:40:53,869
lays the foundation of the promotion of domestic therapeutic apparatus.

510
00:40:53,869 --> 00:40:57,080
The committee members all believe this is the right time.

511
00:40:59,830 --> 00:41:04,340
What about the feedback on the apparatus in commission?

512
00:41:05,290 --> 00:41:06,910
All I need is your approval.

513
00:41:06,910 --> 00:41:12,430
For any problem which may occur, I'll deal with it.

514
00:41:12,430 --> 00:41:13,860
Once I sign these papers,

515
00:41:13,860 --> 00:41:16,700
I'll be the one who takes full responsibility for the problems.

516
00:41:16,700 --> 00:41:19,290
You can rest assured of that. Everything will be fine.

517
00:41:19,290 --> 00:41:22,089
However, it's good to know that you have a sense of responsibility.

518
00:41:22,089 --> 00:41:26,630
So, Mr. Ye, please send me a copy when the data collection is done.

519
00:41:26,630 --> 00:41:28,970
That will be reassuring for me.

520
00:41:40,180 --> 00:41:43,120
How is it going with the files?

521
00:41:43,120 --> 00:41:45,530
Any good news?

522
00:41:47,850 --> 00:41:49,950
Not yet.

523
00:41:51,040 --> 00:41:52,940
I'm sorry.

524
00:41:52,940 --> 00:41:54,550
I see.

525
00:41:54,550 --> 00:41:56,120
You have a million things to do every day.

526
00:41:56,120 --> 00:41:59,950
It would be impossible to cover every single issue in a perfect way.

527
00:41:59,950 --> 00:42:01,650
I understand.

528
00:42:02,770 --> 00:42:04,270
Thanks for understanding.

529
00:42:04,270 --> 00:42:08,120
If there is no other business, I might now take my leave.

530
00:42:08,120 --> 00:42:09,720
Lu Wen,

531
00:42:15,290 --> 00:42:18,180
there is something I want to confirm with you.

532
00:42:21,420 --> 00:42:24,000
We're still

533
00:42:24,880 --> 00:42:28,939
on the same boat, aren't we?

534
00:42:28,939 --> 00:42:34,340
It depends whether we are heading in the same direction.

